definition.value: A taxifolin that has (2S,3R)-configuration.
A dTDP-sugar having 5,5-di-C-methyl-beta-L-lyxose as the sugar component.
A dTDP-sugar having beta-L-vancosamine as the sugar component.
A dTDP-sugar having beta-L-daunosamine as the sugar component.
An arenesulfonic acid that is phenol substituted by a sulfo group at C-4.
A 3-coumaric acid that is phenol substituted with trans-2-propenoic acid at position C-3.
A fatty-acyl group derived from dodecanoic (lauric) acid.
A long-chain fatty acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of icosanoic acid (arachidic acid).
A medium-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of nonanoic acid that in methyl ester form has significant nematicidal activity.
A medium-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of heptanoic acid; shown in myocardial ischaemia/reperfusion studies to increase levels of C4 Kreb's cycle intermediates.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is obtained by removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of 3-dehydroquinic acid.
A C17 saturated fatty acid and trace component of fats in ruminants.
A straight-chain saturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of margaric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A straight-chain, eleven-carbon saturated medium-chain fatty acid found in body fluids; the most fungitoxic of the C7:0 - C18:0 fatty acid series.
A medium-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of undecanoic acid; used in tandem with testosterone cation in the treatment of male hypogonadism. Major species at pH 7.3.
A chalcone that is (E)-chalcone bearing four additional hydroxy substituents at positions 2', 3, 4 and 4'.
A tetradecenoate that is the conjugate base of myristoleic acid.
A hexadec-9-enoate that is the conjugate base of palmitoleic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A coumarate that is the conjugate base of 4-coumaric acid.
The trans-isomer of 4-coumaric acid.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of petroselinic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.
An octadec-6-enoyl group in which the olefinic double bond has Z configuration.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of petroselaidic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.
An octadec-6-enoyl group in which the olefinic double bond has E configuration.
A muconate that is the conjugate base of (2Z,4Z)-5-carboxypenta-2,4-dienoate.

Trimethylamine in which hydrogen atoms attached to different methyl groups are substituted by 1-naphthyl and 4-tert-butylphenyl groups. It is an inhibitor of squalene epoxidase, an enzyme responsible for the creation of sterols needed in fungal cell membranes, and is used as its hydrochloride salt for treatment of dermatological fungal infections.
A decenoic acid having a cis- double bond at position 4.
A decenoic acid having the double bond at position 9.
A mandelate that is the conjugate base of (R)-mandelic acid.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion and the conjugate base of 6-hydroxyhexanoic acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
